# Parameterized Builds

##     Jenkis Pipeline - Parameterized
yo will learn how to **create parameterized buils in Jenkins**.

pipeline{
    agent any
    paramentrs {

        String(name: ENVIOURNMENT', defaultValue: 'dev', description: 'Deployment Environment')
    }
    enviourment {
        INTITUTE_NAME = "pathnex"

    }
    stages {
        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                git url: 'https://github.com/pathnex/sample-java-app,git'
            }
        }
        stage('Deploy') {
             steps {
                        sh 'echo "Deplying to $ ENVIURNMENT by 4INSTITUTE_NAME"'
            }
        }
    }
}

##    GitLab CI - Parameterized via Variables

you will learn how to **use variable to parameterize GitLab Jobs**.

stages:
 - deploy

variables:
  INSTITUTE_NAME: "Pathnex"
  ENVIOURNMENT: "dev"

